would have a segment of increasing slope, where the increasing marginal visibility from particulate
abatement dominates the decreasing marginal utility of additional visibility then, as complete abatement is approached (i.e., somewhere to the right of our point B), the slope may become decreasing
as the diminishing marginal utility of visibility becomes dominant. Such a curve form would be consistent with theoretical considerations and with the three data points available.

