the concept of willingness to pay (which implicitly places the liability with the receptor of damages)
would underestimate both the optimal level of abatement and the appropriate level of fines or taxes.
Randall [15] and others have demonstrated that the demand for abatement of an external diseconomy
is greater in the full liability situation than in the zero liability situation implicit in willingness to
pay games.
